In any cshtml file write this (note there is no space between `@functions` and `{`):
```c#
@page "/"
<h1>Hello</h1>
@functions{
    protected override void OnInit()
    {
        base.OnInit();
        int i = 1;
        if (i != 0)
        {
            Console.WriteLine(i);
        }
    }
}
```
`OnInit` function is correctly indented. Now add space between `@functions` and `{` or move `{` to new line (which is more natural C# formatting) and reformat document.
```c#
@page "/"
<h1>Hello</h1>
@functions
{
protected override void OnInit()
{
    base.OnInit();
    int i = 1;
    if (i != 0)
    {
        Console.WriteLine(i);
    }
}
}
```
This time `OnInit` function is not indented which is wrong.

